Project Overview

The purpose of this project is to design and develop a mobile-first dating application that differentiates itself by offering users the ability to connect through simple, cooperative 2-player games. The app will prioritize minimalism, ease of use, and a professional design aesthetic.

2. Goals & Objectives

Provide a dating platform that is intuitive and safe.

Offer a set of casual cooperative games to facilitate interaction and build connections.

Ensure minimalistic UI/UX with frictionless navigation and a clean aesthetic.

Build a scalable backend capable of supporting matchmaking and multiplayer gameplay.

Launch MVP on iOS and Android.

3. Project Deliverables
Phase 1: Discovery & Design

Branding & Design System

Logo, color palette, typography.

Minimalistic design language (inspired by apps like Tinder, Calm, Duolingo).

Wireframes & Prototypes

Low-fidelity wireframes for core user flows (onboarding, profile creation, matchmaking, game play, chat).

Interactive prototype (Figma or similar) for usability testing.

UI/UX Design

Final high-fidelity designs for all screens.

Responsive mobile-first design guidelines.

Phase 2: Core App Development (MVP)

User Onboarding & Profiles

Account creation (email, phone, social login).

Profile setup (photo upload, bio, interests).

Privacy & safety settings.

Matchmaking & Discovery

Swipe or list-based matching system.

Filters (age, location, interests).

Push notifications for matches and invitations to play.

Cooperative Game Framework

Core multiplayer infrastructure (real-time or turn-based).

At least 3 lightweight 2-player games included in MVP.

MVP Game Specifications
1. Puzzle Connect

Type: Cooperative puzzle-solving.

Duration: 2–3 minutes per round.

Gameplay: Players see different puzzle states and must share clues to solve a shared grid.

Co-op Mechanic: Neither player can solve alone; asymmetric information drives communication.

Tech Needs: 2D grid mechanic, synchronized game state, optional timer.

Design: Minimal, pastel aesthetic, smooth success animations.

2. Guess & Draw

Type: Turn-based drawing & guessing.

Duration: 1–2 minutes per round.

Gameplay: One player draws from a prompt, the other guesses.

Co-op Mechanic: Both must succeed together (drawer communicates, guesser interprets).

Tech Needs: Canvas drawing tool, real-time stroke sync, word bank in backend.

Design: Limited pen colors, playful animations, correct-guess effects.

3. Survival Challenge

Type: Reflex/timing game.

Duration: 1–3 minutes per round.

Gameplay: Both players control avatars dodging obstacles. If one fails, both lose.

Co-op Mechanic: Both must survive together; requires timing and communication.

Tech Needs: Real-time movement sync, collision detection, randomized obstacles.

Design: Flat minimalist style (inspired by Duet), celebratory effects for wins.

Shared Game Principles

Consistent UI framework (avatars, headers, “Play Again”).

Short duration (1–3 min) for replayability.

Flat, minimal art with cohesive color palette.

Modular framework to support future games.

Phase 3: Backend & Infrastructure

Database & API Development

User data, matches, game state management.

Secure authentication & encryption.

Scalable Game Server

Real-time or pseudo-turn-based server setup.

Match session handling.

Analytics & Metrics

Track DAUs, retention, match rate, game completion rate.

Admin dashboard (basic version).

Phase 4: QA & Testing

Unit testing, integration testing, and game mechanics testing.

Usability testing on design and flows.

Security & privacy testing.

Beta release for feedback collection.

Phase 5: Deployment & Handover

Deploy to Apple App Store and Google Play Store.

Provide documentation:

Technical architecture.

Game framework documentation.

Admin instructions.

Knowledge transfer to client or internal team.

4. Technical Requirements

Platforms: iOS & Android (React Native or Flutter recommended).

Backend: Node.js / Python with scalable cloud infrastructure (AWS, GCP, or Firebase).

Database: PostgreSQL + Redis (for matchmaking/game state).

Game Engine: Unity (for advanced games) or lightweight React Native modules (for mini-games).

Design Tools: Figma for UI/UX.

Analytics: Firebase Analytics, Mixpanel, or Amplitude.

5. Project Timeline (Estimated)

Phase 1: Discovery & Design – 3–4 weeks

Phase 2: Core App Development – 10–12 weeks

Phase 3: Backend & Infrastructure – 6 weeks (parallel to Phase 2)

Phase 4: QA & Testing – 3 weeks

Phase 5: Deployment – 1–2 weeks
Total Duration: ~18–20 weeks for MVP

6. Exclusions (Out of Scope for MVP)

Advanced AI-based matchmaking.

Large library of mini-games (MVP will launch with 3 core games).

Web app version (mobile only at first).

IF MORE CONTENT NEEDS TO BE ADDED USE THE str-replace-editor TOOL TO EDIT THE FILE AFTER IT HAS BEEN CREATED.", "path": "CoplayApp/README.md", "file_content": "# Coplay - Dating App with Cooperative Games\n\nA mobile-first dating application that connects users through simple, cooperative 2-player games.\n\n## Project Overview\n\nCoplay differentiates itself by offering users the ability to connect through casual cooperative games, prioritizing minimalism, ease of use, and a professional design aesthetic.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Frontend**: React Native with Expo\n- **Language**: TypeScript\n- **Navigation**: React Navigation (to be added)\n- **State Management**: React Context + Hooks\n- **Backend**: Node.js/Express (to be implemented)\n- **Database**: PostgreSQL + Redis\n- **Real-time**: WebSocket/Socket.io\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 components/ # Reusable UI components\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 screens/ # Screen components\n\u2502 \u251c\u2500\u2500 Auth/ # Authentication screens\n\u2502 \u251c\u2500\u2500 Profile/ # Profile management\n\u2502 \u251c\u2500\u2500 Matching/ # Matchmaking screens\n\u2502 \u251c\u2500\u2500 Games/ # Game lobby and results\n\u2502 \u2514\u2500\u2500 Chat/ # Chat functionality\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 games/ # Game implementations\n\u2502 \u251c\u2500\u2500 PuzzleConnect/ # Cooperative puzzle game\n\u2502 \u251c\u2500\u2500 GuessAndDraw/ # Drawing and guessing game\n\u2502 \u2514\u2500\u2500 SurvivalChallenge/ # Reflex/timing game\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 navigation/ # Navigation configuration\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 services/ # API and external services\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 hooks/ # Custom React hooks\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 contexts/ # React contexts\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 types/ # TypeScript type definitions\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 utils/ # Utility functions\n```\n\n## MVP Games\n\n### 1. Puzzle Connect\n- **Type**: Cooperative puzzle-solving\n- **Duration**: 2\u20133 minutes per round\n- **Gameplay**: Players see different puzzle states and must share clues to solve a shared grid\n- **Co-op Mechanic**: Neither player can solve alone; asymmetric information drives communication\n\n### 2. Guess & Draw\n- **Type**: Turn-based drawing & guessing\n- **Duration**: 1\u20132 minutes per round\n- **Gameplay**: One player draws from a prompt, the other guesses\n- **Co-op Mechanic**: Both must succeed together (drawer communicates, guesser interprets)\n\n### 3. Survival Challenge\n- **Type**: Reflex/timing game\n- **Duration**: 1\u20133 minutes per round\n- **Gameplay**: Both players control avatars dodging obstacles. If one fails, both lose\n- **Co-op Mechanic**: Both must survive together; requires timing and communication\n\n## Development Phases\n\n1. **Phase 1**: Discovery & Design (3-4 weeks)\n2. **Phase 2**: Core App Development (10-12 weeks)\n3. **Phase 3**: Backend & Infrastructure (6 weeks)\n4. **Phase 4**: QA & Testing (3 weeks)\n5. **Phase 5**: Deployment & Handover (1-2 weeks)\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1. Install dependencies:\n ```bash\n npm install\n ```\n\n2. Start the development server:\n ```bash\n npm start\n ```\n\n3. Run on specific platforms:\n ```bash\n npm run ios # iOS simulator\n npm run android # Android emulator\n npm run web # Web browser\n ```\n\n## Design Principles\n\n- **Minimalistic UI/UX** with frictionless navigation\n- **Clean aesthetic** inspired by Tinder, Calm, and Duolingo\n- **Mobile-first** responsive design\n- **Short game duration** (1-3 minutes) for replayability\n- **Consistent game framework** for future scalability\n\n## Contributing\n\nThis project follows a structured development approach with task management and regular progress tracking."}","mcp_server_name":"","mcp_tool_name":""}},{"id":2,"type":0,"content":"Now let me create some essential configuration files and initial architecture documentation:
